@unnumbered Stop mode

@c @man {15}
@c @ifman @unnumberedsubsec Stop
ZDL can be stopped in different ways:
@itemize
@item
If the downloads are managed by the "non-interactive" / standard mode:

@enumerate
@item
typing @kbd {M-k} (in this case all downloads started by ZDL in the specified destination directory or in the current one will be interrupted)

@item
typing @kbd {M-q} (all downloads already started in the current directory will not be interrupted, but will no longer be managed by ZDL until a new instance @emph {standard} or @emph {demon} of the program)
@end enumerate

@item
If the downloads are managed by the "demon" mode:
through the interactive mode @command {zdl -i} started in the directory managed by the daemon, by typing the "Quit" exit key (capitalized, that is, with @kbd {Shift-q}): @kbd {Q} (in this case the downloads started in the directory will not be interrupted, but will not be managed by ZDL unless it is restarted to manage the same downloads)
@end itemize


@c @end man

@htmlend

@node Check the downloads, User manuals, Stop ZDL, Top
